parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Throttle Positioning Sensor (TPS) can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or near-misses, especially when the bike is in motion.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
especially when the clutch is engaged or shifted into neutral
the bike sputters or stalls when idling
the engine RPMs drop to zero
the bike accelerates or decelerates erratically
the engine idles down to 400-500 RPM instead of the usual 11-12K RPM.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Throttle Position Sensor (TPS) can cause poor engine performance, stalling, hesitation, and unpredictable acceleration, which can lead to accidents or loss of control, especially in traffic.
symptoms: Poor gas mileage
engine stalling
hesitation
stuttering
and unpredictable acceleration
especially when initiating throttle from a stop or cruising on the highway.
